article.headline: EIA reports a weekly rise of 70 billion cubic feet in U.S. natural-gas supplies
article.body: The U.S. Energy Information Administration reported Thursday that domestic supplies of natural gas rose by 70 billion cubic feet for the week ended Sept. 4. That was higher than the increase of 64 billion cubic feet forecast by analysts polled by S&P Global Platts. Total stocks now stand at 3.525 trillion cubic feet, up 528 billion cubic feet from a year ago, and 409 billion cubic feet above the five-year average, the government said. October natural gas NGV20, -2.27% was down 5.4 cents, or 2.2%, at $2.352 per million British thermal units. It traded at $2.33 before the data.
